rlAAA.name: rlAAA
rlAAA.description: The private MIB module definition for Authentication, Authorization and Accounting in DLINK-3100 devices.

RlAAAServiceType.name: RlAAAServiceType
RlAAAServiceType.description: Line service type.rlAAAServiceTypeDontCare must be the maximum value in the enum.

RlAAALinePortType.name: RlAAALinePortType
RlAAALinePortType.description: Line physical port type,the rlAAAPortDontCare must be the maximum value in the enum.

rlAAAMibVersion.name: rlAAAMibVersion
rlAAAMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 2. The difference in RlAAALocalLoginHistEntry, RlAAALinePassLoginHistEntry, RlAAASystemLoginHistEntry added mrid field.

rlAAARetries.name: rlAAARetries
rlAAARetries.description: Determines the number of retries for each method (Radius, local passwords, local users table and tacacs).

rlAAARadiusEnabled.name: rlAAARadiusEnabled
rlAAARadiusEnabled.description: Specifies whether AAA will use Radius. When to use Radius exactly depends on its position in the methods list.

rlAAATacacsEnabled.name: rlAAATacacsEnabled
rlAAATacacsEnabled.description: Specifies whether AAA will use Tacacs. When to use Tacacs exactly depends on its position in the methods list.

rlAAALocalUserEnabled.name: rlAAALocalUserEnabled
rlAAALocalUserEnabled.description: Specifies whether AAA will use the local users table. When to use the table exactly depends on its position in the methods list.

rlAAASystemPasswordEnabled.name: rlAAASystemPasswordEnabled
rlAAASystemPasswordEnabled.description: Specifies whether AAA will use the system password. When to use the passwords exactly depends on its position in the methods list.

rlAAALinePasswordEnabled.name: rlAAALinePasswordEnabled
rlAAALinePasswordEnabled.description: Specifies whether AAA will use the line password. When to use the passwords exactly depends on its position in the methods list.

rlAAAAlwaysSuccessEnabled.name: rlAAAAlwaysSuccessEnabled
rlAAAAlwaysSuccessEnabled.description: Specifies whether AAA will use the always success method. When to use that method exactly depends on its position in the methods list.

rlAAARadiusSupported.name: rlAAARadiusSupported
rlAAARadiusSupported.description: This mib show whether Radius is supported in AAA. If the value is false Radius will not be used as an authentication and accounting method. If the value is true Radius will be used by AAA for authentication and accounting if the the AAA was configured to do so (by setting the appropriate mibs).

rlAAATacacsSupported.name: rlAAATacacsSupported
rlAAATacacsSupported.description: This mib show whether Tacacs+ is supported in AAA. If the value is false Tacacs+ will not be used as an authentication and accounting method. If the value is true Tacacs+ will be used by AAA for authentication and accounting if the the AAA was configured to do so (by setting the appropriate mibs).

rlAAALocalUserSupported.name: rlAAALocalUserSupported
rlAAALocalUserSupported.description: This mib show whether the local users db is supported in AAA.If the value is false the local users db will not be used as an authentication and accounting method. If the value is true the local users db will be used by AAA for authentication and accounting method if the the AAA was configured to do so (by setting the appropriate mibs).

rlAAASystemPasswordSupported.name: rlAAASystemPasswordSupported
rlAAASystemPasswordSupported.description: This mib show whether system password is supported in AAA. If the value is false system password will not be used as an authentication and accounting method. If the value is true the system password will be used by AAA for authentication and accounting method if the the AAA was configured to do so (by setting the appropriate mibs).

rlAAALinePasswordSupported.name: rlAAALinePasswordSupported
rlAAALinePasswordSupported.description: This mib show whether line password is supported in AAA. If the value is false line password will not be used as an authentication and accounting method. If the value is true the line password will be used by AAA for authentication and accounting method if the the AAA was configured to do so (by setting the appropriate mibs).

rlAAALineAlwaysSuccessSupported.name: rlAAALineAlwaysSuccessSupported
rlAAALineAlwaysSuccessSupported.description: This mib show whether line always success method is supported in AAA.If the value is false always success method will not be used as an authentication and accounting method. If the value is true the always success method will be used by AAA for authentication and accounting method if the the AAA was configured to do so (by setting the appropriate mibs).

rlAAALinePassword.name: rlAAALinePassword
rlAAALinePassword.description: Line Password. Zero length password is considered as no password. Password with zero length means that in case this password is the method to be used a method fail is returned and no other method is being used. allowed formats: a. Display string starting with '$' for clear text b. Encrypted password: starts with # sign followed by 32 octets representing Hex Decimal value(in the 0-9 a-f A-F range) the $ and # as first octet are a directive to indicate what is the type of password and are not not part of it

rlAAALineStatus.description: Line status can be destroy or createAndGo

rlAAALineConsFailedLogins.description: Number of last consecutive failed logins

rlAAALinePasswordValidTime.name: rlAAALinePasswordValidTime
rlAAALinePasswordValidTime.description: The period of time in days, during which the password, is considered valid for login. Value of 0 means never expired. The actual range is product specific. After this time the system may allow limited number of logins to change the password.

rlAAALinePasswordExpieryDate.name: rlAAALinePasswordExpieryDate
rlAAALinePasswordExpieryDate.description: If Line password aging is active, the date on which The current password will expire. Otherwise zero size string

rlAAAUserEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlAAAUserServiceType.description: The service that the user uses. Service dont care is console terminal.

rlAAAUserLoginDurationMS.name: rlAAAUserLoginDurationMS
rlAAAUserLoginDurationMS.description: Time in MS since user login.

rlAAATestPassword.name: rlAAATestPassword
rlAAATestPassword.description: This variable enables the user supplying the correct code to use the AAA test feature.

rlAAATestUserTable.name: rlAAATestUserTable
rlAAATestUserTable.description: This table enables a user to perform a simulation of authentiction.

rlAAATestUserEntry.name: rlAAATestUserEntry
rlAAATestUserEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlAAATestUserIndex.name: rlAAATestUserIndex
rlAAATestUserIndex.description: User entry index (the number is used just to identify the user).

rlAAATestIfIndex.name: rlAAATestIfIndex
rlAAATestIfIndex.description: line ifIndex can configue to be zero witch means Don't-care value

rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus.name: rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus
rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus.description: Shows the ststus of the operation and what is expected from the 'user'.

rlAAATestUserAuthenticationAction.name: rlAAATestUserAuthenticationAction
rlAAATestUserAuthenticationAction.description: By setting this field the process moves from one state to another. On creation the value must be begin. When the value of rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus is needPassword the value can be set to receivePassword or abort. When the value of rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus is needUsername the value can be set to receiveUsername or abort. When the value of rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus is success or failure the value can be set to delete or abort. When the value of rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus is aborted the value can be set to delete. When the value of rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus is deleted the value can not be set to any value. When the value of rlAAATestUserAuthenticationStatus is waiting the value can be set or abort.

rlAAATestUserInput.name: rlAAATestUserInput
rlAAATestUserInput.description: If the acion was set to receivePassword than this field should hold the value of the password. If the action was set to receiveUsername than this field should hold the value of the username.

rlAAATestUserStatus.name: rlAAATestUserStatus
rlAAATestUserStatus.description: Entry status. The entry can not be deleted. It will be deleted if unchanged more than 2 minutes.

rlRadiusMibVersion.name: rlRadiusMibVersion
rlRadiusMibVersion.description: MIB's version, the current version is 2. 1 - original version. 2 - field rlRadiusServerUsage was added to rlRadiusServerEntry

rlRadiusGlobalDefaultTimeout.name: rlRadiusGlobalDefaultTimeout
rlRadiusGlobalDefaultTimeout.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for this RADIUS server to reply. This MIB is used if the value of the field rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultTimeout is false.

rlRadiusGlobalDefaultRetries.name: rlRadiusGlobalDefaultRetries
rlRadiusGlobalDefaultRetries.description: The number of times to try contacting this RADIUS server. This MIB is used if the value of the field rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultRetries is false.

rlRadiusGlobalDefaultDeadtime.name: rlRadiusGlobalDefaultDeadtime
rlRadiusGlobalDefaultDeadtime.description: Number of minutes that any RADIUS server is ignored after it has failed. This MIB is used if the value of the field rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultDeadtime is false.

rlRadiusGlobalDefaultKey.name: rlRadiusGlobalDefaultKey
rlRadiusGlobalDefaultKey.description: Secret key to be shared with this RADIUS server. This MIB is used if the value of the field rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultKey is false.

rlRadiusGlobalDefaultSource.name: rlRadiusGlobalDefaultSource
rlRadiusGlobalDefaultSource.description: IPv4 address of the interface to use with this server. A value of 0.0.0.0 for this object disables source address specification. This MIB is used if the value of the field rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultSource is false.

rlRadiusServerTable.name: rlRadiusServerTable
rlRadiusServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS servers with which the cliient shares a secret.

rlRadiusServerEntry.name: rlRadiusServerEntry
rlRadiusServerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS server with which the client shares a secret.

rlRadiusServerAddress.name: rlRadiusServerAddress
rlRadiusServerAddress.description: The IP address of the RADIUS server referred to in this table entry.

rlRadiusServerAuthPortNumber.name: rlRadiusServerAuthPortNumber
rlRadiusServerAuthPortNumber.description: The UDP port the client is using to send authentication requests to this server.

rlRadiusServerAcctPortNumber.name: rlRadiusServerAcctPortNumber
rlRadiusServerAcctPortNumber.description: The UDP port the client is using to send accounting requests to this server.

rlRadiusServerTimeout.name: rlRadiusServerTimeout
rlRadiusServerTimeout.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for this RADIUS server to reply. Value of 0 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultTimeout.

rlRadiusServerRetries.name: rlRadiusServerRetries
rlRadiusServerRetries.description: The number of times to try contacting this RADIUS server. Value of 0 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultRetries.

rlRadiusServerDeadtime.name: rlRadiusServerDeadtime
rlRadiusServerDeadtime.description: Number of minutes that any RADIUS server is ignored after it has failed. Value of 2001 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultDeadtime will be used.

rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultKey.name: rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultKey
rlRadiusServerUseGlobalDefaultKey.description: If this field is set to true the value in field rlRadiusServerKey is ignored and instead the value in the MIB rlRadiusGlobalDefaultKey is used. Otherwise the value in rlRadiusServerKey is used.

rlRadiusServerKey.name: rlRadiusServerKey
rlRadiusServerKey.description: Secret key to be shared with this RADIUS server.

rlRadiusServerSource.name: rlRadiusServerSource
rlRadiusServerSource.description: IP address of the interface to use with this server. A value of 0.0.0.0 for this object disables source address specification. Default value of 255.255.255.255 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultSource will be used.

rlRadiusServerPriority.name: rlRadiusServerPriority
rlRadiusServerPriority.description: Determines the order in which the servers will be used, when 0 is the highest priority. If more than one server share the same priority - they will be used in lexicgoraphic order (the order of entries in this table).

rlRadiusServerUsage.name: rlRadiusServerUsage
rlRadiusServerUsage.description: Determines actions for which the radius server will be used.

rlRadiusServerInetTable.name: rlRadiusServerInetTable
rlRadiusServerInetTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the RADIUS servers with which the cliient shares a secret.

rlRadiusServerInetEntry.name: rlRadiusServerInetEntry
rlRadiusServerInetEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS server with which the client shares a secret.

rlRadiusServerInetAddressType.name: rlRadiusServerInetAddressType
rlRadiusServerInetAddressType.description: The Inet address type of RADIUS server reffered to in this table entry .IPv6Z type is not supported.

rlRadiusServerInetAddress.name: rlRadiusServerInetAddress
rlRadiusServerInetAddress.description: The Inet address of the RADIUS server referred to in this table entry.Only one instance of specified address can be added at the same time.

rlRadiusServerInetAuthPortNumber.name: rlRadiusServerInetAuthPortNumber
rlRadiusServerInetAuthPortNumber.description: The UDP port the client is using to send authentication requests to this server.The zero value can be used only if rlRadiusServerInetAcctPortNumber value is not zero.

rlRadiusServerInetAcctPortNumber.name: rlRadiusServerInetAcctPortNumber
rlRadiusServerInetAcctPortNumber.description: The UDP port the client is using to send accounting requests to this server.The zero value can be used only if rlRadiusServerInetAuthPortNumber value is not zero.

rlRadiusServerInetTimeout.name: rlRadiusServerInetTimeout
rlRadiusServerInetTimeout.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for this RADIUS server to reply. Value of 0 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultTimeout.

rlRadiusServerInetRetries.name: rlRadiusServerInetRetries
rlRadiusServerInetRetries.description: The number of times to try contacting this RADIUS server. Value of 0 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultRetries.

rlRadiusServerInetDeadtime.name: rlRadiusServerInetDeadtime
rlRadiusServerInetDeadtime.description: Number of minutes that any RADIUS server is ignored after it has failed. Value of 2001 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultDeadtime will be used.

rlRadiusServerInetUseGlobalDefaultKey.name: rlRadiusServerInetUseGlobalDefaultKey
rlRadiusServerInetUseGlobalDefaultKey.description: If this field is set to true the value in field rlRadiusServerKey is ignored and instead the value in the MIB rlRadiusGlobalDefaultKey is used. Otherwise the value in rlRadiusServerKey is used.

rlRadiusServerInetKey.name: rlRadiusServerInetKey
rlRadiusServerInetKey.description: Secret key to be shared with this RADIUS server.

rlRadiusServerInetSourceType.name: rlRadiusServerInetSourceType
rlRadiusServerInetSourceType.description: The rlRadiusServerInetSource address type. IPv6Z type not supported

rlRadiusServerInetSource.name: rlRadiusServerInetSource
rlRadiusServerInetSource.description: Inet address of the interface to use with this server. To provide backward compatibility the value of 0.0.0.0 for this object will be used to disables source address specification. Default value of 255.255.255.255 means that rlRadiusGlobalDefaultSource will be used for Ipv4 servers and rlRadiusIPv6GlobalDefaultSource will be used for Ipv6 servers.IPv6Z type not supported. Only valid IP address will be used. Application will set default value.

rlRadiusServerInetPriority.name: rlRadiusServerInetPriority
rlRadiusServerInetPriority.description: Determines the order in which the servers will be used, when 0 is the highest priority. If more than one server share the same priority - they will be used in lexicgoraphic order (the order of entries in this table).

rlRadiusServerInetUsage.name: rlRadiusServerInetUsage
rlRadiusServerInetUsage.description: Determines actions for which the radius server will be used. WirelessAuthentication will be used if wireless is supported.

rlTacacsGlobalDefaultSourceIpInterface.description: IP address of the interface to use with TACACS+ server. A value of 0.0.0.0 for this object disables source address specification. This MIB is used if the value of the field rlTacacsServerSource is 255.255.255.255.

rlTacacsServerPriority.description: Determines the order in which the TACACS+ servers will be used, when 0 is the highest priority. If more than one server share the same priority - they will be used in lexicgoraphic order (the order of entries in this table).

The value applies only to new or updated user passwords. In actual implementation the range may be reduced to (0 | N-64), where N is a platform dependent (for TIC compatibility N=8)
